<blockquote>
 <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1"/>
 <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
  The sign for "
  <b>
   <i>
    habit
   </i>
  </b>
  " sort of reminds me of the 
	idea of being "chained" or "bound" to a particular activity.
  <br/>
  This sign can mean "accustomed to" or "used to." The sign moves straight down.
  <p>
   <font face="Arial">
    HABIT:
    <br/>
   </font>
   <img border="0" src="/images/habit.gif" style="max-width: 100%; height: auto" width="480"/>
  </p>
  <p>
   <img border="0" height="222" src="/images/habit1.jpg" width="206"/>
   <img border="0" height="222" src="/images/habit2.jpg" width="206"/>
   <img border="0" height="222" src="/images/habit3.jpg" width="206"/>
   <font face="Arial">
    <br/>
    Memory 
	hint:
  The activities you are "handcuffed to."
    <br/>
    <br/>
    Sample sentence: "Do you have any habits?" = HABIT ANY YOU?
    <br/>
    <br/>
   </font>
