   </object>
  </p>
  <font face="Arial">
   <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1"/>
   <p>
    There is a version of this sign that I label as "ACCUSTOMED- to." It 
	starts with an open dominant hand which changes into a "closed" hand.  
	Lots of people use this sign to mean "habit."
    <br/>
    <br/>
    HABIT / accustomed-to:
    <br/>
    <img border="0" height="320" src="/images/habit.25.jpg" width="268"/>
    <img border="0" height="320" src="/images/habit.26.jpg" width="268"/>
    <img border="0" height="320" src="/images/habit.27.jpg" width="268"/>
   </p>
   <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1"/>
  </font>
  <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
   <br/>
   <font face="Arial">
    Note:
   </font>
   <p style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
    You may see this sign done with a
    <font face="Arial">
     "T" on the dominant hand, if so, it means: "tradition."
     <br/>
    </font>
    <font face="Arial">
     <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1"/>
